  "description": "Sharat Singh Bhandari (born 8 October 1954) is a Nepalese politician and a multi-term minister. He has served as Minister of Labour, Minister of Energy, Minister of Defence, and Minister of Tourism. Bhandari has been elected to the Pratinidhi Sabha multiple times since 1994, representing various constituencies in Mahottari. His political career spans several parties, and he is currently affiliated with the Loktantrik Samajwadi Party. His 18-day tenure as Minister of Energy in 2021 is one of the shortest in Nepal's history.",
